// bisect: NODE-WALK bug, the SHRINK sibling of 01 — soak jul07f
// fuzz/divergence_000000 (found within minutes of the 01 fix
// shipping; the size sequence [0,2,1,4] shrinks 2→1 mid-stream). A
// resize is itself a firing event (the fused loop re-runs every slot
// and fires — SlotFlags' resized channel), but after a SHRINK every
// remaining slot can be quiet (a closed callback whose inputs didn't
// change), so FoldQ's chain gate (`inits.last()`) was None and the
// node-walk skipped the emission the JIT produced: group(f, n==4)
// never completed — interp Trace([]) vs jit [(4, [2,4,2,8])]. FIXED:
// when the chain gate is empty on a resized cycle, emit the HELD
// chain tail — a quiet slot's held value IS what the re-run computes
// (its inputs are unchanged); a bottomed chain has no held tail and
// stays silent, like the kernel's tainted carry.
// mutant: {let a = array::init(array::iter([i64:1, i64:2, i64:1, i64:4]), |i| i + i64:1); let f = array::fold(a, i64:0, |acc, x| acc + i64:2); array::group(f, |n, _| n == i64:4)}
// minimized:
{let a = array::init(array::iter([i64:0, i64:2, i64:1, i64:4]), |i| i + i64:1); let f = array::fold(a, i64:0, |acc, x| acc + i64:2); array::group(f, |n, _| n == i64:4)}
